<p>Proposals</h1></p>

<p>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</p>


<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</ref>
<ref class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</ref>
<p>This article is about the Neil Simon play. For other uses of the word Proposal, see <ref class="mw-redirect mw-disambig" href="/wiki/Proposal_(disambiguation)" title="Proposal (disambiguation)">Proposal (disambiguation)</ref>.</p>
<ref class="image" href="/wiki/File:SimonProposals.JPG"></ref> <ref class="internal" href="/wiki/File:SimonProposals.JPG" title="Enlarge"></ref>
<p>Proposals is a comedy-drama by <ref target="/wiki/Neil_Simon" title="Neil Simon">Neil Simon</ref>, his 30th play. After running in <ref target="/wiki/Los_Angeles" title="Los Angeles">Los Angeles</ref> and the <ref target="/wiki/John_F._Kennedy_Center_for_the_Performing_Arts" title="John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts">Kennedy Center</ref> in 1997, the play opened on <ref target="/wiki/Broadway_theatre" title="Broadway theatre">Broadway</ref> in 1997.</p>

